{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"How will we be remembered in 200 years?"},{"time":3000,"text":"I happen to live in a little town, Princeton, in New Jersey,"},{"time":6000,"text":"which every year celebrates the great event in Princeton history:"},{"time":11000,"text":"the Battle of Princeton, which was, in fact, a very important battle."},{"time":15000,"text":"It was the first battle that George Washington won, in fact,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and was pretty much of a turning point in the war of independence."},{"time":23000,"text":"It happened 225 years ago."},{"time":26000,"text":"It was actually a terrible disaster for Princeton."},{"time":30000,"text":"The town was burned down; it was in the middle of winter,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and it was a very, very severe winter."},{"time":37000,"text":"And about a quarter of all the people in Princeton died that winter"},{"time":41000,"text":"from hunger and cold, but nobody remembers that."},{"time":46000,"text":"What they remember is, of course, the great triumph,"},{"time":48000,"text":"that the Brits were beaten, and we won, and that the country was born."},{"time":56000,"text":"And so I agree very emphatically that the pain of childbirth is not remembered."},{"time":63000,"text":"It's the child that's remembered."},{"time":65000,"text":"And that's what we're going through at this time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"I wanted to just talk for one minute about the future of biotechnology,"},{"time":77000,"text":"because I think I know very little about that -- I'm not a biologist --"},{"time":80000,"text":"so everything I know about it can be said in one minute."},{"time":83000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":86000,"text":"What I'm saying is that we should follow the model"},{"time":89000,"text":"that has been so successful with the electronic industry,"},{"time":93000,"text":"that what really turned computers into a great success, in the world"},{"time":98000,"text":"as a whole, is toys. As soon as computers became toys,"},{"time":103000,"text":"when kids could come home and play with them,"},{"time":106000,"text":"then the industry really took off. And that has to happen with biotech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"There's a huge --"},{"time":112000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":114000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":117000,"text":"-- there's a huge community of people in the world"},{"time":120000,"text":"who are practical biologists, who are dog breeders,"},{"time":123000,"text":"pigeon breeders, orchid breeders, rose breeders,"},{"time":130000,"text":"people who handle biology with their hands,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and who are dedicated to producing beautiful things, beautiful creatures,"},{"time":140000,"text":"plants, animals, pets. These people will be empowered with biotech,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and that will be an enormous positive step"},{"time":153000,"text":"to acceptance of biotechnology."},{"time":157000,"text":"That will blow away a lot of the opposition."},{"time":162000,"text":"When people have this technology in their hands,"},{"time":164000,"text":"you have a do-it-yourself biotech kit, grow your own --"},{"time":172000,"text":"grow your dog, grow your own cat."},{"time":174000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":176000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":180000,"text":"Just buy the software, you design it. I won't say anymore,"},{"time":186000,"text":"you can take it on from there. It's going to happen, and"},{"time":192000,"text":"I think it has to happen before the technology becomes natural,"},{"time":200000,"text":"becomes part of the human condition,"},{"time":203000,"text":"something that everybody's familiar with and everybody accepts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"So, let's leave that aside."},{"time":209000,"text":"I want to talk about something quite different,"},{"time":212000,"text":"which is what I know about, and that is astronomy."},{"time":216000,"text":"And I'm interested in searching for life in the universe."},{"time":220000,"text":"And it's open to us to introduce a new way of doing that,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and that's what I'll talk about for 10 minutes,"},{"time":227000,"text":"or whatever the time remains."},{"time":234000,"text":"The important fact is, that most of the real estate"},{"time":237000,"text":"that's accessible to us -- I'm not talking about the stars,"},{"time":240000,"text":"I'm talking about the solar system, the stuff that's within reach"},{"time":244000,"text":"for spacecraft and within reach of our earthbound telescopes --"},{"time":250000,"text":"most of the real estate is very cold and very far from the Sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"If you look at the solar system, as we know it today,"},{"time":260000,"text":"it has a few planets close to the Sun. That's where we live."},{"time":265000,"text":"It has a fairly substantial number of asteroids between"},{"time":271000,"text":"the orbit of the Earth out through -- to the orbit of Jupiter."},{"time":276000,"text":"The asteroids are a substantial amount of real estate,"},{"time":279000,"text":"but not very large. And it's not very promising for life,"},{"time":284000,"text":"since most of it consists of rock and metal, mostly rock."},{"time":288000,"text":"It's not only cold, but very dry."},{"time":293000,"text":"So the asteroids we don't have much hope for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"There stand some interesting places a little further out:"},{"time":304000,"text":"the moons of Jupiter and Saturn."},{"time":306000,"text":"Particularly, there's a place called Europa, which is --"},{"time":308000,"text":"Europa is one of the moons of Jupiter,"},{"time":311000,"text":"where we see a very level ice surface,"},{"time":316000,"text":"which looks as if it's floating on top of an ocean."},{"time":319000,"text":"So, we believe that on Europa there is, in fact, a deep ocean."},{"time":323000,"text":"And that makes it extraordinarily interesting as a place to explore."},{"time":327000,"text":"Ocean -- probably the most likely place for life to originate,"},{"time":334000,"text":"just as it originated on the Earth. So we would love to explore Europa,"},{"time":341000,"text":"to go down through the ice,"},{"time":343000,"text":"find out who is swimming around in the ocean,"},{"time":346000,"text":"whether there are fish or seaweed or sea monsters --"},{"time":351000,"text":"whatever there may be that's exciting --- or cephalopods."},{"time":357000,"text":"But that's hard to do. Unfortunately, the ice is thick."},{"time":363000,"text":"We don't know just how thick it is, probably miles thick,"},{"time":366000,"text":"so it's very expensive and very difficult to go down there --"},{"time":370000,"text":"send down your submarine or whatever it is -- and explore."},{"time":374000,"text":"That's something we don't yet know how to do."},{"time":377000,"text":"There are plans to do it, but it's hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Go out a bit further, you'll find that beyond the orbit of Neptune,"},{"time":385000,"text":"way out, far from the Sun, that's where the real estate really begins."},{"time":391000,"text":"You'll find millions or trillions or billions of objects which,"},{"time":396000,"text":"in what we call the Kuiper Belt or the Oort Cloud --"},{"time":399000,"text":"these are clouds of small objects which appear as comets"},{"time":405000,"text":"when they fall close to the Sun. Mostly, they just live out there"},{"time":409000,"text":"in the cold of the outer solar system,"},{"time":412000,"text":"but they are biologically very interesting indeed,"},{"time":416000,"text":"because they consist primarily of ice with other minerals,"},{"time":420000,"text":"which are just the right ones for developing life."},{"time":423000,"text":"So if life could be established out there,"},{"time":426000,"text":"it would have all the essentials -- chemistry and sunlight --"},{"time":432000,"text":"everything that's needed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"So, what I'm proposing"},{"time":438000,"text":"is that there is where we should be looking for life, rather than on Mars,"},{"time":442000,"text":"although Mars is, of course, also a very promising and interesting place."},{"time":446000,"text":"But we can look outside, very cheaply and in a simple fashion."},{"time":451000,"text":"And that's what I'm going to talk about."},{"time":455000,"text":"There is a -- imagine that life originated on Europa,"},{"time":460000,"text":"and it was sitting in the ocean for billions of years."},{"time":464000,"text":"It's quite likely that it would move out of the ocean onto the surface,"},{"time":468000,"text":"just as it did on the Earth."},{"time":470000,"text":"Staying in the ocean and evolving in the ocean for 2 billion years,"},{"time":473000,"text":"finally came out onto the land. And then of course it had great --"},{"time":477000,"text":"much greater freedom, and a much greater variety of creatures"},{"time":481000,"text":"developed on the land than had ever been possible in the ocean."},{"time":485000,"text":"And the step from the ocean to the land was not easy, but it happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"Now, if life had originated on Europa in the ocean,"},{"time":495000,"text":"it could also have moved out onto the surface."},{"time":497000,"text":"There wouldn't have been any air there -- it's a vacuum."},{"time":500000,"text":"It is out in the cold, but it still could have come."},{"time":506000,"text":"You can imagine that the plants growing up like kelp"},{"time":510000,"text":"through cracks in the ice, growing on the surface."},{"time":514000,"text":"What would they need in order to grow on the surface?"},{"time":516000,"text":"They'd need, first of all, to have a thick skin to protect themselves"},{"time":522000,"text":"from losing water through the skin."},{"time":528000,"text":"So they would have to have something like a reptilian skin."},{"time":533000,"text":"But better -- what is more important"},{"time":535000,"text":"is that they would have to concentrate sunlight."},{"time":538000,"text":"The sunlight in Jupiter, on the satellites of Jupiter,"},{"time":542000,"text":"is 25 times fainter than it is here,"},{"time":546000,"text":"since Jupiter is five times as far from the Sun."},{"time":548000,"text":"So they would have to have -- these creatures, which I call sunflowers,"},{"time":552000,"text":"which I imagine living on the surface of Europa, would have to have"},{"time":558000,"text":"either lenses or mirrors to concentrate sunlight,"},{"time":562000,"text":"so they could keep themselves warm on the surface."},{"time":566000,"text":"Otherwise, they would be at a temperature of minus 150,"},{"time":570000,"text":"which is certainly not favorable for developing life,"},{"time":573000,"text":"at least of the kind we know."},{"time":575000,"text":"But if they just simply could grow, like leaves,"},{"time":578000,"text":"little lenses and mirrors to concentrate sunlight,"},{"time":581000,"text":"then they could keep warm on the surface."},{"time":584000,"text":"They could enjoy all the benefits of the sunlight"},{"time":589000,"text":"and have roots going down into the ocean;"},{"time":593000,"text":"life then could flourish much more."},{"time":595000,"text":"So, why not look? Of course, it's not very likely"},{"time":598000,"text":"that there's life on the surface of Europa."},{"time":600000,"text":"None of these things is likely, but my,"},{"time":603000,"text":"my philosophy is, look for what's detectable, not for what's probable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"There's a long history in astronomy of unlikely things"},{"time":613000,"text":"turning out to be there. And I mean,"},{"time":615000,"text":"the finest example of that was radio astronomy as a whole."},{"time":618000,"text":"This was -- originally, when radio astronomy began,"},{"time":623000,"text":"Mr. Jansky, at the Bell labs, detected radio waves coming from the sky."},{"time":633000,"text":"And the regular astronomers were scornful about this."},{"time":637000,"text":"They said, \"It's all right, you can detect radio waves from the Sun,"},{"time":643000,"text":"but the Sun is the only object in the universe that's close enough"},{"time":646000,"text":"and bright enough actually to be detectable. You can easily calculate"},{"time":651000,"text":"that radio waves from the Sun are fairly faint,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and everything else in the universe is millions of times further away,"},{"time":661000,"text":"so it certainly will not be detectable."},{"time":663000,"text":"So there's no point in looking.\""},{"time":665000,"text":"And that, of course, that set back the progress of radio astronomy"},{"time":670000,"text":"by about 20 years."},{"time":675000,"text":"Since there was nothing there, you might as well not look."},{"time":678000,"text":"Well, of course, as soon as anybody did look,"},{"time":680000,"text":"which was after about 20 years,"},{"time":683000,"text":"when radio astronomy really took off. Because it turned out"},{"time":685000,"text":"the universe is absolutely full of all kinds of wonderful things"},{"time":689000,"text":"radiating in the radio spectrum, much brighter than the Sun."},{"time":695000,"text":"So, the same thing could be true for this kind of life,"},{"time":700000,"text":"which I'm talking about, on cold objects: that it could in fact"},{"time":704000,"text":"be very abundant all over the universe, and it's not been detected"},{"time":708000,"text":"just because we haven't taken the trouble to look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"So, the last thing I want to talk about is how to detect it."},{"time":717000,"text":"There is something called pit lamping."},{"time":719000,"text":"That's the phrase which I learned from my son George,"},{"time":721000,"text":"who is there in the audience."},{"time":723000,"text":"You take -- that's a Canadian expression."},{"time":730000,"text":"If you happen to want to hunt animals at night,"},{"time":732000,"text":"you take a miner's lamp, which is a pit lamp."},{"time":736000,"text":"You strap it onto your forehead, so you can see"},{"time":739000,"text":"the reflection in the eyes of the animal. So, if you go out at night,"},{"time":743000,"text":"you shine a flashlight, the animals are bright."},{"time":750000,"text":"You see the red glow in their eyes,"},{"time":753000,"text":"which is the reflection of the flashlight."},{"time":755000,"text":"And then, if you're one of these unsporting characters,"},{"time":760000,"text":"you shoot the animals and take them home."},{"time":763000,"text":"And of course, that spoils the game"},{"time":765000,"text":"for the other hunters who hunt in the daytime,"},{"time":767000,"text":"so in Canada that's illegal. In New Zealand, it's legal,"},{"time":772000,"text":"because the New Zealand farmers use this as a way of getting rid of rabbits,"},{"time":777000,"text":"because the rabbits compete with the sheep in New Zealand."},{"time":780000,"text":"So, the farmers go out at night"},{"time":782000,"text":"with heavily armed jeeps, and shine the headlights,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and anything that doesn't look like a sheep, you shoot."},{"time":791000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"So I have proposed to apply the same trick"},{"time":796000,"text":"to looking for life in the universe."},{"time":798000,"text":"That if these creatures who are living on cold surfaces --"},{"time":801000,"text":"either on Europa, or further out, anywhere where you can live"},{"time":805000,"text":"on a cold surface -- those creatures must be provided with reflectors."},{"time":811000,"text":"In order to concentrate sunlight, they have to have lenses and mirrors --"},{"time":814000,"text":"in order to keep themselves warm."},{"time":816000,"text":"And then, when you shine sunlight at them,"},{"time":820000,"text":"the sunlight will be reflected back,"},{"time":823000,"text":"just as it is in the eyes of an animal."},{"time":828000,"text":"So these creatures will be bright against the cold surroundings."},{"time":832000,"text":"And the further out you go in this, away from the Sun,"},{"time":836000,"text":"the more powerful this reflection will be. So actually,"},{"time":840000,"text":"this method of hunting for life gets stronger and stronger"},{"time":843000,"text":"as you go further away,"},{"time":845000,"text":"because the optical reflectors have to be more powerful so the reflected light"},{"time":850000,"text":"shines out even more in contrast against the dark background."},{"time":856000,"text":"So as you go further away from the Sun,"},{"time":858000,"text":"this becomes more and more powerful."},{"time":862000,"text":"So, in fact, you can look for these creatures with telescopes from the Earth."},{"time":868000,"text":"Why aren't we doing it? Simply because nobody thought of it yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"But I hope that we shall look, and with any --"},{"time":877000,"text":"we probably won't find anything,"},{"time":879000,"text":"none of these speculations may have any basis in fact."},{"time":883000,"text":"But still, it's a good chance. And of course, if it happens,"},{"time":886000,"text":"it will transform our view of life altogether."},{"time":889000,"text":"Because it means that -- the way life can live out there,"},{"time":894000,"text":"it has enormous advantages as compared with living on a planet."},{"time":897000,"text":"It's extremely hard to move from one planet to another."},{"time":901000,"text":"We're having great difficulties at the moment"},{"time":905000,"text":"and any creatures that live on a planet are pretty well stuck."},{"time":909000,"text":"Especially if you breathe air,"},{"time":911000,"text":"it's very hard to get from planet A to planet B,"},{"time":914000,"text":"because there's no air in between. But if you breathe air --"},{"time":920000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":925000,"text":"-- you're dead --"},{"time":926000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":928000,"text":"-- as soon as you're off the planet, unless you have a spaceship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"But if you live in a vacuum, if you live on the surface"},{"time":935000,"text":"of one of these objects, say, in the Kuiper Belt,"},{"time":938000,"text":"this -- an object like Pluto, or one of the"},{"time":941000,"text":"smaller objects in the neighborhood of Pluto,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and you happened -- if you're living on the surface there,"},{"time":947000,"text":"and you get knocked off the surface by a collision,"},{"time":950000,"text":"then it doesn't change anything all that much."},{"time":953000,"text":"You still are on a piece of ice, you can still have sunlight"},{"time":957000,"text":"and you can still survive while you're traveling from one place to another."},{"time":961000,"text":"And then if you run into another object, you can stay there"},{"time":965000,"text":"and colonize the other object. So life will spread, then,"},{"time":968000,"text":"from one object to another. So if it exists at all in the Kuiper Belt,"},{"time":972000,"text":"it's likely to be very widespread. And you will have then"},{"time":975000,"text":"a great competition amongst species -- Darwinian evolution --"},{"time":980000,"text":"so there'll be a huge advantage to the species"},{"time":983000,"text":"which is able to jump from one place to another"},{"time":987000,"text":"without having to wait for a collision. And there'll be advantages"},{"time":991000,"text":"for spreading out long, sort of kelp-like forest of vegetation."},{"time":998000,"text":"I call these creatures sunflowers."},{"time":1000000,"text":"They look like, maybe like sunflowers."},{"time":1003000,"text":"They have to be all the time pointing toward the Sun,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and they will be able to spread out in space,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"because gravity on these objects is weak."},{"time":1013000,"text":"So they can collect sunlight from a big area."},{"time":1016000,"text":"So they will, in fact, be quite easy for us to detect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020000,"text":"So, I hope in the next 10 years, we'll find these creatures,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and then, of course, our whole view of life in the universe will change."},{"time":1028000,"text":"If we don't find them, then we can create them ourselves."},{"time":1032000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1035000,"text":"That's another wonderful opportunity that's opening."},{"time":1042000,"text":"We can -- as soon as we have a little bit more understanding"},{"time":1045000,"text":"of genetic engineering, one of the things you can do with your"},{"time":1050000,"text":"take-it-home, do-it-yourself genetic engineering kit --"},{"time":1053000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":1055000,"text":"is to design a creature that can live on a cold satellite,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"a place like Europa, so we could colonize Europa with our own creatures."},{"time":1063000,"text":"That would be a fun thing to do."},{"time":1067000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1070000,"text":"In the long run, of course,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"it would also make it possible for us to move out there."},{"time":1078000,"text":"What's going to happen in the end,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"it's not going to be just humans colonizing space,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"it's going to be life moving out from the Earth,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"moving it into its kingdom. And the kingdom of life,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"of course, is going to be the universe. And if life is already there,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"it makes it much more exciting, in the short run."},{"time":1098000,"text":"But in the long run, if there's no life there, we create it ourselves."},{"time":1104000,"text":"We transform the universe into something much more rich and beautiful"},{"time":1108000,"text":"than it is today."},{"time":1110000,"text":"So again, we have a big and wonderful future to look forward."},{"time":1115000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1116000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}